<p><b>Max Horkheimer</b> (February 14, 1895 – July 7, 1973) was a <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> <a href="/wiki/Philosopher" title="Philosopher" class="mw-redirect">philosopher</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sociologist" title="Sociologist" class="mw-redirect">sociologist</a>, and a founding member of the <a href="/wiki/Frankfurt_School" title="Frankfurt School">Frankfurt School</a>).</p>
